  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency multisectoral response in the territories of Walikale and Masisi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project presented here is complementary to a multisectoral project in response to the immediate needs of the most vulnerable populations in North Kivu funded by the GAC.
ACF will work in collaboration with the BCZS and the IPS North Kivu for support of 1100 cases of MAS (+ buffer of 300 cases for disengagement), whether they come from the populations displaced, returned or hosts. To limit the spread of diarrhoeal diseases and the risk of epidemics, the intervention of ACF will be to ensure an effective emergency response to displacement of populations by providing vital access to water, sanitation, and hygiene in internal displaced persons sites and hosts and resident communities.</narrative>
  </description>
